00:00:00.510 --> 00:00:03.620
Sony Xperia T3 review: Wits and looks.

00:00:03.620 --> 00:00:08.770
Sony's Xperia T lineup has been growing out
of 007's tux and the third generation is putting

00:00:08.770 --> 00:00:09.770
on a t-shirt.

00:00:09.770 --> 00:00:16.180
OK, an oversized t-shirt, although the T3
has lost some weight, and screen real-estate,

00:00:16.180 --> 00:00:17.750
compared to the T2.

00:00:17.750 --> 00:00:22.540
Gone is the Ultra moniker and the massive
6" display - the Xperia T3 is closer to smartphones

00:00:22.540 --> 00:00:24.070
than phablets.

00:00:24.070 --> 00:00:28.160
It is indeed that simple, the Sony Xperia
T3 is a more compact version of the Xperia

00:00:28.160 --> 00:00:31.859
T2 Ultra phablet, one that you can slip in
your pocket.

00:00:31.859 --> 00:00:36.600
The screen is still a high-quality IPS unit
of 720p resolution and Sony once again goes

00:00:36.600 --> 00:00:38.680
for the Snapdragon 400.

00:00:38.680 --> 00:00:43.160
The Xperia T3 is running KitKat out of the
box which is good, but other specs are taken

00:00:43.160 --> 00:00:44.660
a notch down.

00:00:44.660 --> 00:00:51.049
The camera, to begin with, is now an 8MP unit,
down from 13MP in the T2 Ultra.

00:00:51.049 --> 00:00:54.909
On the upside, the proper shutter key is there.

00:00:54.909 --> 00:00:59.710
With a 2,500mAh battery, the Xperia T3 will
probably struggle to match the impressive

00:00:59.710 --> 00:01:03.969
times of the T2 Ultra, but we'd be happy if
it gets close enough.

