00:01:54.409 --> 00:01:58.890
The Sony Xperia T3 seems reasonably equipped
for the midrange and does well to offer LTE

00:01:58.890 --> 00:02:02.100
connectivity on top of good looks and solid
build.

00:02:02.100 --> 00:02:06.750
It's also one of the thinnest Sony smartphones
around with only the Z Ultra having a thinner

00:02:06.750 --> 00:02:07.750
profile.

00:02:07.750 --> 00:02:11.340
The sealed battery should hardly be a surprise,
we guess it's part of the price you are paying

00:02:11.340 --> 00:02:13.120
for the Omni Balance design.

00:02:13.120 --> 00:02:17.840
That said, we have perhaps seen too much of
it already, though it isn't something to hold

00:02:17.840 --> 00:02:22.409
against a device of the Xperia T3's price
bracket and level of equipment.

00:02:22.409 --> 00:02:23.989
Design and handling.

00:02:23.989 --> 00:02:28.079
It's not like we haven't seen the OmniBalance
design used on a plethora of Xperia smartphones

00:02:28.079 --> 00:02:30.209
over the past few years.

00:02:30.209 --> 00:02:34.319
It's probably time the next flagship moved
on but the midrange Xperia T3 is on the safe

00:02:34.319 --> 00:02:35.379
side.

00:02:35.379 --> 00:02:38.019
It looks reasonably good and has pleasant
handling.

00:02:38.019 --> 00:02:42.200
The Sony Xperia T3's entire front is occupied
by the 5.3" IPS display.

00:02:42.200 --> 00:02:48.719
The non-removable rear cover is made of plastic,
with matte finish in graphite black.

00:02:48.719 --> 00:02:53.019
The material doesn't look or feel low quality,
but fingerprints tend to stick on.

00:02:53.019 --> 00:02:56.810
They would probably be harder to notice on
the white and purple versions.

00:02:56.810 --> 00:03:01.700
Still, the issue is not as obvious as it would
have been on a glossy surface.

00:03:01.700 --> 00:03:06.249
Just like most of the previous Xperia phones,
the Xperia T3 sides are lined with a glossy

00:03:06.249 --> 00:03:08.900
strip for a nice contrasting accent.

00:03:08.900 --> 00:03:12.529
The only thing actually made of metal is the
signature power/lock key.

00:03:12.529 --> 00:03:17.469
Handling the Sony Xperia T3 is a pleasure
and the screen size isn't a particular burden.

00:03:17.469 --> 00:03:23.700
With a 7mm waistline, the Xperia T3 feels
great in hand, not bulky at all, and well

00:03:23.700 --> 00:03:26.059
put together, no wobbles or squeaks.

00:03:26.059 --> 00:03:29.819
In fact, it's among the thinnest Sony phones
ever.

